§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬real linear transformation❭ is a function $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥^m$
    satisfying
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(αx + βy) =αf(x) + βf(y). ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ Equivalently, $f$ is (a) homogenous $f(αx) = αf(x)$ and (b)
    additive $f(x + y)= f(x) + f(y)$. ⦉
